Truckin’ … heading down to Miami for some sun! Three dogs means we’re driving 🚌🐕‍🦺🐻🐕‍🦺 

Stops in Wilmington/ Chadds Ford for Neff family Christmas, and one more roadside stop for some rest in … Smithfield, NC.

22 hours from Boston to Miami, So lots of comedy and podcasts needed to keep us going. Send some entertainment suggestions if you have any. 
10 hours to go!
Happy New Year! Love you all. See you soon!

In the middle of an epic road trip from Boston to Miami and back we made a stop in Palm Beach for an incredible stay and meal at @thecolonypalmbeach and @swiftyspb .

First time in Palm Beach, FL and at the Colony Hotel and I was happily surprised. We stayed with our three dogs in a Villa Suite… the hotel is super dog friendly, which as all dog parents know, can make or break a trip. 

We were only in town for 20 hours but fit a lot in.

Dinner at the hotel’s restaurant @swiftyspb was insanely good and the service was amazing.

Took a 5 mile jog around the island , a dip in the pool, had some breakfast with family and walked the dogs around town, all in the matter of a few hours before checking out and hitting the road again.

Thank you so much for taking care of us @mcarfrae and the team. You are the very best!

I’ve been noticing a bunch of friends sustain injuries recently while working out, skiing, or playing their respective sports so it felt appropriate to pay forward a bit of medical help I received not too long ago.

As you may know, tennis is a huge passion of mine and has been a major part of my life since I started competing at 10 years old and went on to play D1 college tennis.

A few years ago I had to play far less due to a shoulder injury— and put off getting treatment for it because I was still able to work out. I really just couldn’t hit a serve.  Surgery would have sidelined me for a while from all activities, including work and working out.

I did some research, asked around, and as luck would have it, a good friend of mine, @dr.kohler brought me up to speed on the benefits of regenerative medicine and treatments, like PRP injections, which Dr. Kohler has been doing at @ospinamedical. So we went ahead and did the procedure on my SLAP Tear, as my injury was called, and I’ve been playing pain-free tennis ever since.

Platelet-Rich Plasma (PRP) injections are minimally invasive and actually allows your body to heal itself. If you are suffering from a sports-related injury or even just joint pain, I highly recommend looking into it, and if in the New York area, check out @ospinamedical and my buddy Dr. Kohler.

One of the reasons I moved to New England, after years in New York, is because I longed for the excitement you can get from daily outdoor adventures. 

As a kid, I first experienced New England while visiting family during Vermont’s Winter and Martha’s Vineyard’s Summers.

The travel added to the appeal. Months of anticipation, then hours of heightened senses set you up, and gathering at a family house or resort with access to daily adventures would send us over the edge.

Wherever you may be traveling from, the energy of Cape Cod and the Islands is buzzing once summer arrives after the cold months build the local resident character along the New England coast.

The location and charm of Wequassett Resort is unmatched. It feels like the most perfectly quintessential historic New England luxe summer village with all of the modern touches and flavors you want from a resort stay.

We played golf, tennis, hiked and went swimming during the day… had massages and great meals waterside in a protected cove on Pleasant Bay near Chatham, MA as the sun went down.

I had never heard of Wequassett Resort before a friend reached out last month. The weather was looking great around my birthday on April 12th so we decided to make the hour trip down Massachusetts Route 3 from the south shore of Boston, where we live (It would have been just another 25 minutes or so if we were coming from Boston Logan Airport) 

They took excellent care of us at every step, arrival to departure, thanks to the experienced and detail oriented staff and crew, and a @barbour experience they’ve put together… the dogs were welcomed with open arms, healthy treats, new water bowls and soft beds as well.

Work has enabled me to experience some of the best resorts available, including the Northeast US, and I would pick Wequassett as one of maybe a couple to represent New England.

Definitely make some time if you’re looking for the fully luxe New England summer vibe.  I will definitely be back soon to check out the property and it’s impeccable blooms this season and beyond.

Thanks to @wequassett and their whole team, @gueystar @barbour and @lecollectivem for making our stay so memorable.

☀️ 🕶️ 🗞️ 🌊 🏖️ 💦 

Thanks again @wequassett @barbour @gueystar @lecollectivem we’ll be back…
